      "digest": {
        "published": "2025-08-22",
        "description": "The LogIn-SignUp project by VishnuSivadasVS is vulnerable to SQL Injection due to unsafe construction of SQL queries in DataBase.php. The functions logIn() and signUp() build queries by directly concatenating user input and unvalidated table names without using prepared statements. While a prepareData() function exists, it is insufficient to prevent SQL injection and does not sanitize the table name.",
        "title": "vishnusivadas login-signup SQL Injection",
        "vendor": "vishnusivadas",
        "product": "login-signup",
        "attack_type": "SQL Injection",
        "cvss_max": 9.8
      },
      "cve": {
        "id": "CVE-2025-51092",
        "sourceIdentifier": "cve@mitre.org",
        "published": "2025-08-22T19:15:39.470",
        "lastModified": "2025-10-09T18:00:31.943",
        "vulnStatus": "Analyzed",
        "descriptions": [
          {
            "lang": "en",
            "value": "The LogIn-SignUp project by VishnuSivadasVS is vulnerable to SQL Injection due to unsafe construction of SQL queries in DataBase.php. The functions logIn() and signUp() build queries by directly concatenating user input and unvalidated table names without using prepared statements. While a prepareData() function exists, it is insufficient to prevent SQL injection and does not sanitize the table name."
          },
          {
            "lang": "es",
            "value": "El proyecto LogIn-SignUp de VishnuSivadasVS es vulnerable a la inyección SQL debido a la construcción insegura de consultas SQL en DataBase.php. Las funciones logIn() y signUp() generan consultas concatenando directamente la entrada del usuario y los nombres de tabla no validados, sin usar sentencias preparadas. Si bien existe la función prepareData(), esta no es suficiente para prevenir la inyección SQL y no depura el nombre de la tabla."
          }
        ],
        "metrics": {
